node.text: Celebrating the incredible people of Walt Disney Animation Studios. ⭐ Foam Laohachaiaroon, Simulation Performance Lead

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Walt Disney Animation Studios on June 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Foam Laohachaiaroon SIMULATION PERFORMANCE LEAD WADiSNEy ANIMATION STUDIOS'.

Photo by Walt Disney Animation Studios on June 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'FOAM LAOHACHAIAROON Tell us about yourself! Hey there! My name is Natnicha Laohachaiaroon but everyone knows me as Foam. was originally from Phichit, a smal town in the middle of Thailand. I'm fortunate enough to get to come to study animation in the United States and work at Disney Animation! @AIdDiSNEyANIMATIONSTUDIOS WADiSNEY ANIMATION STUDIOS'.

Photo by Walt Disney Animation Studios on June 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'FOAM LAOHACHAIAROON What were your dreams as a kid? was I was just kid who would want to just have fun. enjoyed playing games and learning new technology with my dad! didn't have an ultimate goal when kid. Time passed by and got to learn and discovered a lot of other fun stuff and was still interested in technology related to computer graphics. didn't even know that could work in the animation industry! But once had learned about it, started to pursue an animation career. WALrdiSNEy ANIMATION STUDIOS'.

Photo by Walt Disney Animation Studios on June 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'FOAM LAOHACHAIAROON Who inspired you growing up and what was their impact on you? My dad always brought home the newest technology like a DVD player, new computers, new audio systems, and even new versions of TV all the time! It gave me exposure to how the world had been evolving quickly even though we lived in very small town in the countryside. He always inspired me with his knowledge and he showed me that you don't need to focus onjust one thing that you like. Do what you enjoy but also with responsibility. WALdiISNEy ANIMATION STUDIOS'.

Photo by Walt Disney Animation Studios on June 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'FOAM LAOHACHAIAROON What advice would you give someone interested in a career in animation? There are lot of aspects to making animation as well as many styles. Do research on how animation is made and you might be able to find couple of aspects of the process that spark your interest. You might be interested in the technology side, artistic side, or even both! It combination of art and technology after all. WADiSnEy ANIMATION STUDIOS'.

Photo by Walt Disney Animation Studios on June 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'FOAM LAOHACHAIAROON What advice would you give your younger self? Don't be afraid to be different. It's ok if you are still finding your path and you feel that others might already find their path. Focus on yourself. Everyone is not the same so take your time. Oh! And workout more! WALDiSNEy ANIMATION STUDIOS'.

Photo by Walt Disney Animation Studios on June 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'FOAM LAOHACHAIAROON When was a moment that you felt Pride? My parents are very accepting even though know sometimes they need more time to process it. have been very fortunate that they always try to guide, understand and support me and my siblings even if our decisions will conflict with their perspective. Words cannot describe how much am proud and love them. WArdiSNEy ANIMATION ÛITUDIS STUDIOS'.

Photo by Walt Disney Animation Studios on June 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'FOAM LAOHACHAIAROON What are you looking forward to in the future? I'm looking forward to being able to spend more time with my family since they are living across the country currently. hope traveling will be a lot easier for both ends and we get to go on more trips together! WDIISUDIS WALDiSNEY ANIMATION STUDIOS'.
